31/01/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- The European Commission's television channel, Euronews, began broadcasting news in Turkish on Saturday (January 30th), following a ceremony in Istanbul.
Euronews, which is based in Lyon, already offers broadcasts in Arabic, English, French, German, Italian, Spanish, Portuguese and Russian.
Turkey's state-controlled television and radio broadcaster TRT signed an agreement with Euronews in 2008, becoming its fourth biggest partner with a stake of 15.7%.
Euronews has a total of 21 shareholders, including leading European TV channels.
(AFP, Euronews - 30/01/10;
World Bulletin, Euronews - 29/01/10)
